.TH BOOKOKRAT 1 "2026-05-06" "0.3.10" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bookokrat \- terminal EPUB/PDF reader with Vim-style navigation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bookokrat
[\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bookokrat
is a fast terminal UI reader for EPUB and PDF documents.
It presents a split layout with a library/table-of-contents panel on the left
and the document reader on the right.
.PP
When invoked without arguments bookokrat scans the current directory for
EPUB and PDF files and opens the most recently read book automatically.
Passing a file path on the command line opens that document directly.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.SS Global
.TP
.B q
Quit the application.
.TP
.B ?
Toggle the help popup (shows full key reference with ANSI art).
.TP
.B Tab
Switch focus between the navigation panel and the content view.
.TP
.B Esc
Close the current popup, cancel selection, or exit search mode.
.SS Navigation panel
.TP
.B j / k
Move down / up in the book list or table of contents.
.TP
.B b
Toggle between book list and table of contents.
.TP
.B H / L
Collapse / expand all table-of-contents entries.
.TP
.B Enter
Select the highlighted book or chapter.
.SS Reader
.TP
.B j / k
Scroll down / up one line.
.TP
.B h / l
Jump to the previous / next chapter.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-d / Ctrl\-u
Scroll half a screen down / up with a visual highlight.
.TP
.B gg
Jump to the top of the chapter (type g twice within one second).
.TP
.B G
Jump to the bottom of the chapter.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-o / Ctrl\-i
Navigate backward / forward through the jump list.
.TP
.B /
Enter search mode.
.TP
.B n / N
Jump to the next / previous search match.
.TP
.B a
Add or edit an inline comment on the selected text.
.TP
.B d
Delete the comment at the cursor position.
.TP
.B c
Copy the current text selection to the clipboard.
.SS Space-prefixed commands
.TP
.B Space h
Toggle the reading history popup.
.TP
.B Space d
Show book statistics (chapter and screen counts).
.TP
.B Space o
Open the current book in the default system EPUB/PDF viewer.
.TP
.B Space s
Toggle raw HTML view (EPUB only).
.TP
.B Space c
Copy the entire chapter text (EPUB) or extract the page text (PDF).
.TP
.B Space f
Reopen the last book-wide search.
.TP
.B Space F
Start a new book-wide search.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I bookmarks.json
Reading position bookmarks stored in the directory where bookokrat is run.
.TP
.I .bookokrat_comments/
Per-book annotation files in YAML format, stored alongside
.IR bookmarks.json .
.TP
.I ~/.config/bookokrat/config.yaml
Application settings (theme, margins, PDF options).
.TP
.I ~/.config/bookokrat/keybindings.yaml
Optional keybinding overrides in neovim-compatible notation.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TERM, COLORTERM, TERM_PROGRAM
Used to detect terminal capabilities and select the appropriate image
rendering protocol (Kitty, Sixel, iTerm2, or halfblocks).
